Package net.fabricmc.fabric.api.dimension.v1

Class FabricDimensionType.Builder

java.lang.Object
net.fabricmc.fabric.api.dimension.v1.FabricDimensionType.Builder
Enclosing class:
FabricDimensionType
public static final class FabricDimensionType.Builder
extends Object
A builder for creating and registering FabricDimensionType instances. Example: 
   

   public static final FabricDimensionType MY_DIMENSION
       = FabricDimensionType.builder()
           .defaultPlacement((oldEntity, destination, portalDir, horizontalOffset, verticalOffset) ->
           		new BlockPattern.TeleportTarget(new Vec3d(0, 100, 0), teleported.getVelocity(), 0))
           .factory(MyDimension::new)
           .skyLight(true)
           .buildAndRegister();

Builder instances can be reused; it is safe to call buildAndRegister(Identifier) multiple times (with different identifiers) to build and register multiple dimension types in series. Each new dimension type uses the settings of the builder at the time it is built.

See Also:
FabricDimensionType.builder()

  • Method Details

    • defaultPlacer

      public FabricDimensionType.Builder defaultPlacer​(EntityPlacer defaultPlacer)
      Set the default placer used when teleporting entities to dimensions of the built type. The default placer must be set before building a dimension type.

      A dimension type's default placer must never return null when its placeEntity method is called.

      Parameters:
      defaultPlacer - a default entity placer for dimensions of the built type
      Returns:
      this Builder object
      Throws:
      NullPointerException - if defaultPlacer is null

      this Builder object

    • skyLight

      public FabricDimensionType.Builder skyLight​(boolean skyLight)
      Set whether built dimension types use skylight like the Overworld. If this method is not called, the value defaults to true.
      Parameters:

    • biomeAccessStrategy

      public FabricDimensionType.Builder biomeAccessStrategy​(net.minecraft.world.biome.source.BiomeAccessType biomeAccessStrategy)
      Governs how biome information is retrieved from random seed and world coordinates. If this method is not called, value defaults to the three-dimensional strategy used by the End and Nether dimensions.

    • desiredRawId

      public FabricDimensionType.Builder desiredRawId​(int desiredRawId)
      Sets this dimension's desired raw id. If this method is not called, the value defaults to the raw registry id of the dimension type.

      A Fabric Dimension's desired raw id is used as its actual raw id when it does not conflict with any existing id, and the world save does not map the dimension to a different raw id.

      Parameters:
      desiredRawId - the new raw id for this dimension type
      Returns:
      this Builder object

    • buildAndRegister

      public FabricDimensionType buildAndRegister​(net.minecraft.util.Identifier dimensionId)
      Build and register a FabricDimensionType.

      The dimensionId is used as a registry ID, and as a unique name both for the dimension suffix and the save directory.

      Parameters:
      dimensionId - the id used to name and register the dimension
      Returns:
      the built FabricDimensionType
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if an existing dimension has already been registered with dimensionId
      IllegalStateException - if no factory or default placer have been set
